wfFrIfDlcmiTable.name: wfFrIfDlcmiTable
wfFrIfDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface

wfFrIfDlcmiEntry.name: wfFrIfDlcmiEntry
wfFrIfDlcmiEntry.description: The parameters for a particular Data Link Connection Management Interface

wfFrDlcmiDelete.name: wfFrDlcmiDelete
wfFrDlcmiDelete.description: Indication to delete this frame relay interface

wfFrDlcmiDisable.name: wfFrDlcmiDisable
wfFrDlcmiDisable.description: Indicates when a dlcmi entry is to be enabled or disabled.

wfFrDlcmiLineNumber.name: wfFrDlcmiLineNumber
wfFrDlcmiLineNumber.description: The line number on which this frame relay interface resides. This is the first of two instance identifiers.

wfFrDlcmiLLIndex.name: wfFrDlcmiLLIndex
wfFrDlcmiLLIndex.description: The Lower layer index uniquely identifies the lower layer in cases where the lower layer may be something other than the physical layer. For example if Frame Relay is running over an ATM VC, the LLIndex identifies the ATM VC.

wfFrDlcmiCircuit.name: wfFrDlcmiCircuit
wfFrDlcmiCircuit.description: The circuit number of this entry

wfFrDlcmiManagementType.name: wfFrDlcmiManagementType
wfFrDlcmiManagementType.description: This variable indicates which Data Link Connection Management scheme is active (and by implication, what DLCI it uses).

wfFrDlcmiStatus.name: wfFrDlcmiStatus
wfFrDlcmiStatus.description: Indicates the state of the interface. It is called status because this is what it was called in the rfc. FR_STATUS_RUNNING is the sate after the circuit is up (either LMI successful or there is no DLCMI and the system just comes up). FR_STATUS_FAULT is a transient state indicating that errors have caused the circuit to be disabled until DLCMI recovery. FR_STATUS_INITIALIZING is a transient state indicating that the interface is trying to come up. FR_STATUS_NOTPRESENT indicates that the interface is not present. Likely this will never be seen except upon initial configuration.

wfFrDlcmiAddress.name: wfFrDlcmiAddress
wfFrDlcmiAddress.description: This states which address format is in use on the FR interface. The default is Q922

wfFrDlcmiAddressLen.name: wfFrDlcmiAddressLen
wfFrDlcmiAddressLen.description: This variable states the address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address includeding the control portion.

wfFrDlcmiPollingInterval.name: wfFrDlcmiPollingInterval
wfFrDlcmiPollingInterval.description: The number of seconds between successive status enquiry messages

wfFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.name: wfFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval
wfFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.description: The number of status enquiry intervals that pass before issuance of a full status enquiry message.

wfFrDlcmiErrorThreshold.name: wfFrDlcmiErrorThreshold
wfFrDlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept before declaring the interface down.

wfFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.name: wfFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents
wfFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.description: This is the number of status polling intervals over which the error threshold is counted. For example, if within 'MonitoredEvents' number of events the station receives 'ErrorThreshold' number of errors, the interface is marked as down.

wfFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.name: wfFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs
wfFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.description: The maximum number of Virtual Circuits allowed for this interface. Usually dictated by the Frame Relay network. The system sets this initially.

wfFrDlcmiVCsConfigured.name: wfFrDlcmiVCsConfigured
wfFrDlcmiVCsConfigured.description: The number of VCs that are presently configured on the interface.

wfFrDlcmiMulticast.name: wfFrDlcmiMulticast
wfFrDlcmiMulticast.description: This indicates whether the frame relay provider offers a multicast

wfFrDlcmiSeqCount.name: wfFrDlcmiSeqCount
wfFrDlcmiSeqCount.description: This station's sequence counter. It represents the next value to send.

wfFrDlcmiLastReceived.name: wfFrDlcmiLastReceived
wfFrDlcmiLastReceived.description: The sequence number just received from the switch.

wfFrDlcmiPassiveSeqCount.name: wfFrDlcmiPassiveSeqCount
wfFrDlcmiPassiveSeqCount.description: This station's sequence counter for answering status enquiry.

wfFrDlcmiPassiveReceived.name: wfFrDlcmiPassiveReceived
wfFrDlcmiPassiveReceived.description: The sequence number just received from the enquring station.

wfFrDlcmiPolls.name: wfFrDlcmiPolls
wfFrDlcmiPolls.description: This is the counter of where we are in the polling cycle.

wfFrDlcmiCongestionDisable.name: wfFrDlcmiCongestionDisable
wfFrDlcmiCongestionDisable.description: This indicates whether the VCs should use the congestion algorithm or not. Each VC may be configured to run the algorithm to override this setting. Those VCs which are configured via the DLCMI interface, will use this setting as their default.

wfFrDlcmiCongestionTmr.name: wfFrDlcmiCongestionTmr
wfFrDlcmiCongestionTmr.description: This is the time period over which congestion notifications are counted. It is also the period during which the VC will cease sending information before resuming transmission if no congestion notifications are received. The timer is kept in 1/2 second intervals.

wfFrDlcmiCongestionCtr.name: wfFrDlcmiCongestionCtr
wfFrDlcmiCongestionCtr.description: This represents the number of congestion notifications, when received within wfFrDlcmiCongestionTmr time, will result in the VC ceasing transmissions.

wfFrErrType.name: wfFrErrType
wfFrErrType.description: Indicate the type of the last specific monitored error.

wfFrErrData.name: wfFrErrData
wfFrErrData.description: Contains as much of the error packet as possible.

wfFrErrTime.name: wfFrErrTime
wfFrErrTime.description: The time the last error occurred.

wfFrErrDiscards.name: wfFrErrDiscards
wfFrErrDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames dropped because of format or other errors or because the VC was not known.

wfFrErrDrops.name: wfFrErrDrops
wfFrErrDrops.description: The number of outbound frames dropped. Usually this is due the specified DLCI being unknown or a broadcast packet is too long

wfFrErrFaults.name: wfFrErrFaults
wfFrErrFaults.description: The number of times that the Interface has come down due to errors since the system started. The value is reset when a restart parameter is modified.

wfFrErrFaultTime.name: wfFrErrFaultTime
wfFrErrFaultTime.description: The time at which the interface last went down.

wfFrDlcmiDialFailureDisable.name: wfFrDlcmiDialFailureDisable
wfFrDlcmiDialFailureDisable.description: On a dial interface, this indicates whether to time-out if a full status message is not received. A timeout will cause the connection to terminate.

wfFrDlcmiInterfaceType.name: wfFrDlcmiInterfaceType
wfFrDlcmiInterfaceType.description: Indicates the type of interface this is. A normal interface is not backed up, a primary interface is backed up, and a backup interface is used for backup. backupDup is a cue for SiteManager.

wfFrDlcmiBackupFilterCct.name: wfFrDlcmiBackupFilterCct
wfFrDlcmiBackupFilterCct.description: The circuit number which defines the ppq filters that the backup interface will use. If 0, the filters defined for the default/main circuit will be used.

wfFrDlcmiDebugLevel.name: wfFrDlcmiDebugLevel
wfFrDlcmiDebugLevel.description: For Bay Networks internal use only.

wfFrDlcmiTraceLevel.name: wfFrDlcmiTraceLevel
wfFrDlcmiTraceLevel.description: For Bay Networks internal use only.

wfFrDlcmiCongestionMethod.name: wfFrDlcmiCongestionMethod
wfFrDlcmiCongestionMethod.description: Default congestion control method to use for all VCs on this interface.

wfFrDlcmiShapingTmr.name: wfFrDlcmiShapingTmr
wfFrDlcmiShapingTmr.description: The interval, in ticks (1/1024th of a second), that VCs are processed for traffic shaping.

wfFrDlcmiShapingHiQueueLimit.name: wfFrDlcmiShapingHiQueueLimit
wfFrDlcmiShapingHiQueueLimit.description: The total number of buffers that the interface will allow VCs to queue into the Hi queue. Divided by the number of traffic shaped VCs to get the number of buffers allowed per-VC.

wfFrDlcmiShapingNormalQueueLimit.name: wfFrDlcmiShapingNormalQueueLimit
wfFrDlcmiShapingNormalQueueLimit.description: The total number of buffers that the interface will allow VCs to queue into the Normal queue. Divided by the number of traffic shaped VCs to get the number of buffers allowed per-VC.

wfFrDlcmiShapingLoQueueLimit.name: wfFrDlcmiShapingLoQueueLimit
wfFrDlcmiShapingLoQueueLimit.description: The total number of buffers that the interface will allow VCs to queue into the Lo queue. Divided by the number of traffic shaped VCs to get the number of buffers allowed per-VC.

wfFrDlcmiXoffDisable.name: wfFrDlcmiXoffDisable
wfFrDlcmiXoffDisable.description: Indicates whether to listen(enabled) or ignore(disabled) XOFF (R-bit) notification

wfFrDlcmiMissingPolls.name: wfFrDlcmiMissingPolls
wfFrDlcmiMissingPolls.description: Number of times there was no status enquiry response to a status enquiry

wfFrDlcmiName.name: wfFrDlcmiName
wfFrDlcmiName.description: User name for this interface, used by BCC

wfFrDlcmiEnableSinglePVCUpdate.name: wfFrDlcmiEnableSinglePVCUpdate
wfFrDlcmiEnableSinglePVCUpdate.description: Enables or disables the processing of Single Async PVC status messages that some switches use. If disabled, Single Async PVC status messages are ignored. All status changes in the FR circuit are based on the processing of full status enquiry response messages.

wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnq.name: wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnq
wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnq.description: Enables or disables the processing of status enquiry on annexdswitch(7) and annexaswitch(8). If it is enabled and the status enquiry is not received from the DTE within wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnqTmr, the internal counter will be incremented. If internal counter exceeds wfFrDlcmiErrorThreshold, the circuit will be brought down.

wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnqTmr.name: wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnqTmr
wfFrDlcmiAnnexSwEnqTmr.description: Specify the timeout value in seconds for the status inquiry on annexdswitch(7) and annexaswitch(8). It is defaulted to 10 seconds.

wfFrDlcmiExtraStatusInfoEnable.name: wfFrDlcmiExtraStatusInfoEnable
wfFrDlcmiExtraStatusInfoEnable.description: Indicates whether or not to process extra lmi ies that may received from the switch

wfFrVCircuitTable.name: wfFrVCircuitTable
wfFrVCircuitTable.description: Frame Relay Circuit table gives information about a virtual circuits.

wfFrVCircuitEntry.name: wfFrVCircuitEntry
wfFrVCircuitEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Circuit table.

wfFrCircuitDelete.name: wfFrCircuitDelete
wfFrCircuitDelete.description: Indication to delete this frame relay interface.

wfFrCircuitLineNumber.name: wfFrCircuitLineNumber
wfFrCircuitLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This is the line number on which the associated Frame Relay interface resides.

wfFrCircuitLLIndex.name: wfFrCircuitLLIndex
wfFrCircuitLLIndex.description: The Lower layer index uniquely identifies the lower layer in cases where the lower layer may be something other than the physical layer. For example if Frame Relay is running over an ATM VC, the LLIndex identifies the ATM VC.

wfFrCircuitNumber.name: wfFrCircuitNumber
wfFrCircuitNumber.description: The circuit number of this interface.

wfFrCircuitDlci.name: wfFrCircuitDlci
wfFrCircuitDlci.description: One of three instance identifier. This is the Frame Relay 'address' of the virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitState.name: wfFrCircuitState
wfFrCircuitState.description: Indicates the state of the particular virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitStateSet.name: wfFrCircuitStateSet
wfFrCircuitStateSet.description: User access for setting the state of a virtual circuit

wfFrCircuitReceivedFECNs.name: wfFrCircuitReceivedFECNs
wfFrCircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received indicating forward congestion.

wfFrCircuitReceivedBECNs.name: wfFrCircuitReceivedBECNs
wfFrCircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received indicating backward congestion.

wfFrCircuitSentFrames.name: wfFrCircuitSentFrames
wfFrCircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitSentOctets.name: wfFrCircuitSentOctets
wfFrCircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitReceivedFrames.name: wfFrCircuitReceivedFrames
wfFrCircuitReceivedFrames.description: The number of frames received from this virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitReceivedOctets.name: wfFrCircuitReceivedOctets
wfFrCircuitReceivedOctets.description: The number of octets received from this virtual circuit.

wfFrCircuitCreationTime.name: wfFrCircuitCreationTime
wfFrCircuitCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the vc was created.

wfFrCircuitLastTimeChange.name: wfFrCircuitLastTimeChange
wfFrCircuitLastTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when last there was a change in vc state.

wfFrCircuitCommittedBurst.name: wfFrCircuitCommittedBurst
wfFrCircuitCommittedBurst.description: Indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

wfFrCircuitExcessBurst.name: wfFrCircuitExcessBurst
wfFrCircuitExcessBurst.description: Indicates teh maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will attempt to deliver over the measurement interval.

wfFrCircuitThroughput.name: wfFrCircuitThroughput
wfFrCircuitThroughput.description: This is the average number of 'Frame Relay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement interval.

wfFrCircuitMulticast.name: wfFrCircuitMulticast
wfFrCircuitMulticast.description: Indicates whether this DLCI is used for multicast or single destination.

wfFrCircuitType.name: wfFrCircuitType
wfFrCircuitType.description: Indication of whether the VC was manually created (static), or dynamically created (dynamic) via the data link control management interface.

wfFrCircuitDiscards.name: wfFrCircuitDiscards
wfFrCircuitDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames discarded because of format errors, because the VC is inactive or because the protocol was not registered for this circuit.

wfFrCircuitDrops.name: wfFrCircuitDrops
wfFrCircuitDrops.description: Indicates how many outbound frames were dropped. Usually these are dropped because the VC is not active.

wfFrCircuitSubCct.name: wfFrCircuitSubCct
wfFrCircuitSubCct.description: Circuit number to use for this VC when configured in hybrid (for bridging) or direct access (VC as a circuit) mode.

wfFrCircuitMode.name: wfFrCircuitMode
wfFrCircuitMode.description: The mode of the given VC. GROUP - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit. HYBRID - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit for protocol traffic, but as a separate circuit for bridging. DIRECT - treats the VC as a separate circuit for all applications.

wfFrCircuitCongestionDisable.name: wfFrCircuitCongestionDisable
wfFrCircuitCongestionDisable.description: This indicates whether the congestion algorithm should be used for this VC. If this is not set, the value is inherited from the DLCMI record.

wfFrCircuitCongestionState.name: wfFrCircuitCongestionState
wfFrCircuitCongestionState.description: This is used to indicate whether or not the VC is in a congested state. If it is, no traffic will be sent on this VC.

wfFrCircuitCongestionTmr.name: wfFrCircuitCongestionTmr
wfFrCircuitCongestionTmr.description: This is the time period over which congestion notifications are counted. It is also the period during which the VC will cease sending information before resuming transmission if no congestion notifications are received.

wfFrCircuitCongestionCtr.name: wfFrCircuitCongestionCtr
wfFrCircuitCongestionCtr.description: This represents the number of congestion notifications, when received within wfFrCircuitCongestionTmr time, that will result in the VC ceasing transmissions.

wfFrCircuitPrimaryHoldTmr.name: wfFrCircuitPrimaryHoldTmr
wfFrCircuitPrimaryHoldTmr.description: The maximum number of seconds that a Frame Relay PVC Primary will be kept inactive, ignoring status messages, when it is terminated because the backup has started.

wfFrCircuitInactivityTimer.name: wfFrCircuitInactivityTimer
wfFrCircuitInactivityTimer.description: Inactivity Timer for SVCs. Zero disables timer.

wfFrCircuitInactivityMode.name: wfFrCircuitInactivityMode
wfFrCircuitInactivityMode.description: Specifies which packets will reset the SVC inactivity timer.

wfFrCircuitCongestionMethod.name: wfFrCircuitCongestionMethod
wfFrCircuitCongestionMethod.description: The congestion method to use on this VC.

wfFrCircuitShapedHiXmits.name: wfFrCircuitShapedHiXmits
wfFrCircuitShapedHiXmits.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsHiXmits for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedNormalXmits.name: wfFrCircuitShapedNormalXmits
wfFrCircuitShapedNormalXmits.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsNormalXmits for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedLoXmits.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLoXmits
wfFrCircuitShapedLoXmits.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLoXmits for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedHiClippedPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedHiClippedPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedHiClippedPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsHiClippedPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedNormalClippedPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedNormalClippedPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedNormalClippedPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsNormalClippedPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedLoClippedPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLoClippedPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedLoClippedPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLoClippedPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedHiQHighWaterPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedHiQHighWaterPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedHiQHighWaterPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsHiQHighWaterPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedLoQHighWaterPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLoQHighWaterPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedLoQHighWaterPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLoQHighWaterPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedDroppedPkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedDroppedPkts
wfFrCircuitShapedDroppedPkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsDroppedPkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedLargePkts.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLargePkts
wfFrCircuitShapedLargePkts.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLargePkts for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedHiTotalOctets.name: wfFrCircuitShapedHiTotalOctets
wfFrCircuitShapedHiTotalOctets.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsHiTotalOctets for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedNormalTotalOctets.name: wfFrCircuitShapedNormalTotalOctets
wfFrCircuitShapedNormalTotalOctets.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsNormalTotalOctets for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedLoTotalOctets.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLoTotalOctets
wfFrCircuitShapedLoTotalOctets.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLoTotalOctets for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedPktsNotQueued.name: wfFrCircuitShapedPktsNotQueued
wfFrCircuitShapedPktsNotQueued.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsPktsNotQueued for this VC

wfFrCircuitShapedHiQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitShapedHiQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitShapedHiQueueLimit.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsHighPriorityQueueLimit for this VC. If set to inherit (0), then the VC uses part of the global allocation of buffers in the DLCMI entry.

wfFrCircuitShapedNormalQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitShapedNormalQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitShapedNormalQueueLimit.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsNormalPriorityQueueLimit for this VC. If set to inherit (0), then the VC uses part of the global allocation of buffers in the DLCMI entry.

wfFrCircuitShapedLoQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitShapedLoQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitShapedLoQueueLimit.description: Same as wfCctOptsEntry.wfCctOptsLowPriorityQueueLimit for this VC. If set to inherit (0), then the VC uses part of the global allocation of buffers in the DLCMI entry.

wfFrCircuitStartupDelay.name: wfFrCircuitStartupDelay
wfFrCircuitStartupDelay.description: Number of seconds the VC should wait before creating the circuit or doing a dp_vc_line.

wfFrCircuitCurHiQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitCurHiQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitCurHiQueueLimit.description: This is the current high queue limit, based on the VC and DLCMI configuration.

wfFrCircuitCurNormalQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitCurNormalQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitCurNormalQueueLimit.description: This is the current normal queue limit, based on the VC and DLCMI configuration.

wfFrCircuitCurLoQueueLimit.name: wfFrCircuitCurLoQueueLimit
wfFrCircuitCurLoQueueLimit.description: This is the current low queue limit, based on the VC and DLCMI configuration.

wfFrCircuitShapingState.name: wfFrCircuitShapingState
wfFrCircuitShapingState.description: Indicates current state of a VCs traffic shaping configuration

wfFrCircuitBwThreshold.name: wfFrCircuitBwThreshold
wfFrCircuitBwThreshold.description: Set 3 to 10 times of the CIR configured with this PVC. The threshold value for starting to send Normal and Low Priority traffic is calculated based on physical line speed. Setting this object to 3 to 10 times of CIR value will provide more chance to the Normal and Low Priority traffic so that it will help the Normal and Low Priority traffic of low speed links over high speed physical line from starvation such as 56Kbps and 65Kbps lines over HSSI.

wfFrCircuitReceivedDEs.name: wfFrCircuitReceivedDEs
wfFrCircuitReceivedDEs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating that they were eligible for discard since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the remote DTE sets the DE flag, or when in remote DTE's switch detects that the frame was received as Excess Burst data.

wfFrCircuitSentDEs.name: wfFrCircuitSentDEs
wfFrCircuitSentDEs.description: Number of frames sent from the network indicating that they were eligible for discard since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the local DTE sets the DE flag, indicating that during Network congestion situations those frames should be discarded in preference of ther frames sent without the DE bit set.

wfFrCctErrorTable.name: wfFrCctErrorTable
wfFrCctErrorTable.description: The Frame Relay Circuit Error Table.

wfFrCctErrorEntry.name: wfFrCctErrorEntry
wfFrCctErrorEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Circuit Error table.

wfFrCctErrorCct.name: wfFrCctErrorCct
wfFrCctErrorCct.description: Instance Identifier - indicates the frame relay circuit number

wfFrCctErrorDrops.name: wfFrCctErrorDrops
wfFrCctErrorDrops.description: Indicates the number of frames that were dropped at the circuit level. Generally this is because the particular protocol (within the inbound frame) was not registered for this circuit.

wfFrCctErrorDiscards.name: wfFrCctErrorDiscards
wfFrCctErrorDiscards.description: Indicates the number of frames that were discarded at the circuit level. Generally this is because the outbound frame was too long, or too short.

wfFrServiceRecordTable.name: wfFrServiceRecordTable
wfFrServiceRecordTable.description: Frame Relay service records group virtual circuits together.

wfFrServiceRecordEntry.name: wfFrServiceRecordEntry
wfFrServiceRecordEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Service Record table.

wfFrServiceRecordDelete.name: wfFrServiceRecordDelete
wfFrServiceRecordDelete.description: Indication to delete this frame relay service record.

wfFrServiceRecordLineNumber.name: wfFrServiceRecordLineNumber
wfFrServiceRecordLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This is the line number on which the associated Frame Relay interface resides.

wfFrServiceRecordLLIndex.name: wfFrServiceRecordLLIndex
wfFrServiceRecordLLIndex.description: The Lower layer index uniquely identifies the lower layer in cases where the lower layer may be something other than the physical layer. For example if Frame Relay is running over an ATM VC, the LLIndex identifies the ATM VC.

wfFrServiceRecordCircuitNumber.name: wfFrServiceRecordCircuitNumber
wfFrServiceRecordCircuitNumber.description: The circuit number of this interface.

wfFrServiceRecordDefaultFlag.name: wfFrServiceRecordDefaultFlag
wfFrServiceRecordDefaultFlag.description: Identifies default service record for VCs added via the frame relay switch.

wfFrServiceRecordNumberVCs.name: wfFrServiceRecordNumberVCs
wfFrServiceRecordNumberVCs.description: Number of virtual circuit associated with a service record.

wfFrServiceRecordState.name: wfFrServiceRecordState
wfFrServiceRecordState.description: Used to identify new service record instances

wfFrServiceRecordPreMultiCircuit.name: wfFrServiceRecordPreMultiCircuit
wfFrServiceRecordPreMultiCircuit.description: circuit number prior to enabling multiline, allows restoration of pre-multiline circuit

wfFrServiceRecordBackupFilterCct.name: wfFrServiceRecordBackupFilterCct
wfFrServiceRecordBackupFilterCct.description: The circuit number used by the backup interface to store/define the ppq filter configuration.

wfFrServiceRecordBackupLineNumber.name: wfFrServiceRecordBackupLineNumber
wfFrServiceRecordBackupLineNumber.description: Indicates one of the backup interfaces for this primary interface. The circuit on this service record should be shared onto that backup interface.

wfFrServiceRecordBackupLLIndex.name: wfFrServiceRecordBackupLLIndex
wfFrServiceRecordBackupLLIndex.description: Indicates one of the backup interfaces for this primary interface. The circuit on this service record should be shared onto that backup interface.

wfFrServiceRecordBackupMainCct.name: wfFrServiceRecordBackupMainCct
wfFrServiceRecordBackupMainCct.description: Indicates the main circuit of one of the backup interfaces for this primary interface. The circuit on this service record should be shared onto that backup interface.

wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLineNumber.name: wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLineNumber
wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLineNumber.description: Indicates the primary interface for this backup interface This should be set only in the Default Service Record.

wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLLIndex.name: wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLLIndex
wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryLLIndex.description: Indicates the primary interface for this backup interface. This should be set only in the Default Service Record.

wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryMainCct.name: wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryMainCct
wfFrServiceRecordPrimaryMainCct.description: Indicates the main circuit on the primary interface for this backup interface. This should be set only in the Default Service Record.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCDisable.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCDisable
wfFrServiceRecordSVCDisable.description: Allow SVCs on this service record.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocNum.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocNum
wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocNum.description: Number associated with this service record.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocSubAdr.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocSubAdr
wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocSubAdr.description: Subaddress of type NSAP (Q.931) further qualifies number

wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocPlan.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocPlan
wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocPlan.description: Supported Q.931 4.3.8/4.3.10 numbering plans. Each plan is represented by the 4 least significant bits to align with the values stated in Q.931.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocTypeNum.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocTypeNum
wfFrServiceRecordSVCLocTypeNum.description: Supported Q.931 4.3.8/4.3.10 types of number. Each type is represented by a value one greater than the values stated in Q.931.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCCallBlock.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCCallBlock
wfFrServiceRecordSVCCallBlock.description: Allow all calls, block inbound, block outbound, block all calls.

wfFrServiceRecordSVCInactTimer.name: wfFrServiceRecordSVCInactTimer
wfFrServiceRecordSVCInactTimer.description: Inactivity Timer for SVCs. Zero disables timer.

wfFrServiceRecordNumberStaticVCs.name: wfFrServiceRecordNumberStaticVCs

wfFrMapCircuitState.name: wfFrMapCircuitState
wfFrMapCircuitState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational. In the absence of a Data Link Connection Management Interface, virtual circuit entries (rows) may be created by setting virtual circuit state to 'active', or deleted by changing Circuit state to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation, so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time. It is also legal to set the state of a virtual circuit to 'inactive' to temporarily disable a given circuit. The use of 'invalid' is deprecated in this SNMP Version 2 MIB, in favor of frCircuitRowStatus.

wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFECNs.name: wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFECNs
wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating forward congestion since the virtual circuit was created. wfFrMapCircuitReceivedBECNs.name: wfFrMapCircuitReceivedBECNs
wfFrMapCircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating backward congestion since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the remote DTE sets the BECN flag, or when a switch in the network receives the frame from a trunk whose transmission queue is congested

wfFrMapCircuitSentFrames.name: wfFrMapCircuitSentFrames
wfFrMapCircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit since it was created. Octets counted are the full frame relay header and the payload, but do not include the flag characters or CRC.

wfFrMapCircuitSentOctets.name: wfFrMapCircuitSentOctets
wfFrMapCircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created. Octets counted are the full frame relay header and the payload, but do not include the flag characters or CRC.

wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFrames.name: wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFrames
wfFrMapCircuitReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

wfFrMapCircuitReceivedOctets.name: wfFrMapCircuitReceivedOctets
wfFrMapCircuitReceivedOctets.description: Number of octets received over this virtual circuit since it was created. Octets counted include the full frame relay header, but do not include the flag characters or the CRC.

wfFrMapCircuitCreationTime.name: wfFrMapCircuitCreationTime

wfFrMapCircuitCommittedBurst.name: wfFrMapCircuitCommittedBurst
wfFrMapCircuitCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

wfFrMapCircuitExcessBurst.name: wfFrMapCircuitExcessBurst
wfFrMapCircuitExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will attempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

wfFrMapCircuitThroughput.name: wfFrMapCircuitThroughput
wfFrMapCircuitThroughput.description: Throughput is the average number of 'Frame Relay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement interval. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both non-zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=frCircuitCommittedBurst/frCircuitThroughput. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=frCircuitExcessBurst/ifSpeed.

wfFrMapCircuitMulticast.name: wfFrMapCircuitMulticast

wfFrMapCircuitType.description: Indication of whether the VC was manually created (static), or dynamically created (dynamic) via the data link control management interface.

wfFrMapCircuitDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames dropped because of format errors, or because the VC is inactive.

wfFrMapErrData.name: wfFrMapErrData

wfFrMapErrTime.name: wfFrMapErrTime

wfFrMapErrFaults.name: wfFrMapErrFaults
wfFrMapErrFaults.description: The number of times the interface has gone down since it was initialized.

wfFrMapErrFaultTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the interface was taken down due to excessive errors.
